---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LeadForm from '../components/LeadForm.astro';

const phone = "(801) 514-7004";
const phoneHref = "tel:+18015147004";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Roofing Services | Sandy Roofing Pros — Sandy, UT"
  description="Emergency roof leak repair, storm damage restoration, and roof inspections serving Sandy and Salt Lake County, Utah. Licensed local contractors available 24/7."
  canonicalUrl="/services"
>

  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Roofing Services — Sandy &amp; Salt Lake County, UT</h1>
      <p>
        Active leak, storm damage, or a roof you haven't thought about in ten years —
        here's what local roofers in our area actually do, and when you need them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== EMERGENCY LEAK REPAIR ===== -->
  <section class="service-section" id="emergency-leak">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-section__inner">
        <div>
          <div class="service-section__icon">🚨</div>
          <span class="service-section__badge">Most Urgent</span>
          <h2>Emergency Roof Leak Repair</h2>
          <p>
            3 a.m. and water is dripping into your kitchen. It happens more than you'd think
            out here — a late October storm rolls through the valley fast, and by morning
            you've got a wet ceiling and no idea where it's coming from.
          </p>
          <p>
            The problem isn't just the wet spot. It's what happens when that water sits:
            insulation that has to be replaced, drywall that buckles, wood that warps.
            Mold shows up faster than most people expect. <strong>Roofers in our area are
            available around the clock</strong> — when you call, you reach someone who can
            actually get out, not a voicemail box.
          </p>
          <ul class="service-bullets">
            <li>Same-day response — nights and weekends included</li>
            <li>Emergency tarping first, permanent repair when conditions allow</li>
            <li>Find the actual source — not just patch what's visible</li>
            <li>Written documentation for your insurance claim</li>
          </ul>
          <a href={phoneHref} class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">
            📞 Call Now for Emergency Help
          </a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="background:#FEF2F2; border:1px solid #FECACA; border-radius:8px; padding:2rem;">
            <h3 style="color:#B91C1C; margin-bottom:1rem;">Stop and Call If You See Any of This</h3>
            <ul class="service-bullets">
              <li>Water dripping from the ceiling or a light fixture</li>
              <li>A stain spreading on drywall after rain</li>
              <li>Sagging or bubbling ceiling after heavy snow</li>
              <li>Daylight visible through the attic boards</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="margin-top:1rem; font-size:0.9rem; color:#7F1D1D;">
              These aren't "keep an eye on it" situations. Each one gets worse fast.
              Call now — same-day help is available.
            </p>
            <a href={phoneHref} class="btn btn--primary btn--block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
              📞 {phone}
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== STORM DAMAGE REPAIR ===== -->
  <section class="service-section" id="storm-damage">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-section__inner">
        <div>
          <div style="background:#FFFBEB; border:1px solid #FDE68A; border-radius:8px; padding:2rem;">
            <h3 style="color:#92400E; margin-bottom:1rem;">Does Your Home Qualify for an Insurance Claim?</h3>
            <p style="font-size:0.9rem; color:#78350F; margin-bottom:1rem;">
              A lot of Sandy homeowners don't realize storm damage is covered until it's
              too late to file. The window matters. Roofers in our area know what adjusters
              look for and can help you move quickly:
            </p>
            <ul class="service-bullets">
              <li>Photos and measurements that hold up with an adjuster</li>
              <li>Written damage report in the format insurers want</li>
              <li>On-site adjuster walk-through if needed</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="#contact-section" class="btn btn--accent btn--block" style="margin-top:1.25rem; color:#1E293B;">
              Get a Free Damage Assessment
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="service-section__icon">🌩️</div>
          <span class="service-section__badge">Insurance-Assisted</span>
          <h2>Storm Damage Roof Repair</h2>
          <p>
            A July hailstorm in Sandy can drop golf ball-sized hail in fifteen minutes
            and move on. Your roof takes the hit. From the street it looks fine.
            Up close, the granules are knocked loose, the shingles are bruised, and
            you've lost years off the life of that roof — probably without knowing it.
          </p>
          <p>
            Wind damage is subtler. A lifted shingle in the 84070 zip lets water
            under the deck for months before you see a stain inside. Local roofers
            know what to look for — and know how to get it covered.
          </p>
          <ul class="service-bullets">
            <li>Hail and wind damage assessment with documentation</li>
            <li>Shingle, flashing, and gutter repair</li>
            <li>Full replacement when the damage warrants it</li>
            <li>Post-storm inspection before you file any claim</li>
          </ul>
          <a href={phoneHref} class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">
            📞 Get a Free Storm Assessment
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== ROOF INSPECTION ===== -->
  <section class="service-section" id="roof-inspection">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-section__inner">
        <div>
          <div class="service-section__icon">🔍</div>
          <span class="service-section__badge">Preventative</span>
          <h2>Roof Inspections</h2>
          <p>
            Utah winters don't forgive a bad roof. Snowpack sits up there for weeks.
            Ice dams form at the eaves. One small flashing gap that didn't matter
            in August will be leaking by February — and by then it's an emergency
            instead of a $300 repair.
          </p>
          <p>
            A fall inspection takes an hour. A roofer gets up there, checks the
            shingles, flashing, gutters, and attic, and tells you exactly what
            you're dealing with. If something needs fixing, you handle it before
            the snow flies. If everything's solid, you have peace of mind for the season.
          </p>
          <ul class="service-bullets">
            <li>Shingles, flashing, valleys, and gutters checked from the surface</li>
            <li>Attic moisture and ventilation inspection</li>
            <li>Written report with photos — useful for home sales and insurance</li>
            <li>Honest lifespan estimate, no upsell</li>
          </ul>
          <a href={phoneHref} class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">
            📞 Schedule a Roof Inspection
          </a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="background:#F0FDF4; border:1px solid #BBF7D0; border-radius:8px; padding:2rem;">
            <h3 style="color:#14532D; margin-bottom:1rem;">Good Times to Schedule One</h3>
            <ul class="service-bullets">
              <li>Before or after buying a home</li>
              <li>After a hail or windstorm — even if nothing looks wrong</li>
              <li>Roof is 10+ years old and hasn't been looked at</li>
              <li>You're seeing granules building up in the gutters</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lead Form -->
  <section class="section section--alt" id="contact-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-heading__eyebrow">Free Estimate</span>
        <h2>Tell Us About Your Roof — Get Help Fast</h2>
      </div>
      <LeadForm
        title="Request a Free Estimate"
        subtitle="A licensed Salt Lake County roofing contractor will contact you shortly."
      />
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
